azoo\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"Implement the following plan:\\n\\n# Refactor `CalculateTokenUsage` to accept `[]byte` and use canonical interface\\n\\n## Context\\n\\n`TokenCalculator.CalculateTokenUsage` currently takes a file path (`sessionRef string`) and each agent reads the file internally. Meanwhile, the condensation code in the strategy package has its own `calculateTokenUsage` helper that dispatches by `agentType` to package-level functions, bypassing the interface entirely. This refactoring:\\n\\n1. Changes the interface to accept `data []byte` so callers that already have bytes (condensation) don't need file I/O\\n2. Makes the strategy's helper use the canonical `TokenCalculator` interface via `agent.GetByAgentType`\\n\\n## Changes\\n\\n### 1. Interface signature (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go:169`)\\n\\n```go\\n// Before\\nCalculateTokenUsage(sessionRef string, fromOffset int) (*TokenUsage, error)\\n// After\\nCalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*TokenUsage, error)\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Claude Code implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go:131-138`)\\n\\nReplace file-based delegation with bytes-based parsing:\\n```go\\nfunc (c *ClaudeCodeAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to parse transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n    }\\n    if fromOffset > 0 && fromOffset < len(lines) {\\n        lines = lines[fromOffset:]\\n    }\\n    return CalculateTokenUsage(lines), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: This does NOT include subagent tokens. The subagent-aware path is handled separately by `SubagentAwareExtractor.CalculateTotalTokenUsage` which lifecycle.go already prefers. That interface is not changed.\\n\\n### 3. Gemini CLI implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go:99-102`)\\n\\nDelegate to the existing bytes-based package-level function:\\n```go\\nfunc (g *GeminiCLIAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\\n    return CalculateTokenUsage(data, fromOffset), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n(The package-level `geminicli.CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, startMessageIndex int)` already accepts bytes.)\\n\\n### 4. OpenCode implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/transcript.go:295-322`)\\n\\nDelegate to the existing `CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes`:\\n```go\\nfunc (a *OpenCodeAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\\n    return CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes(data, fromOffset), nil\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Lifecycle caller (`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:357-365`)\\n\\nPass `transcriptData` (already loaded at line 193) instead of `transcriptRef`:\\n```go\\nusage, tokenErr := calculator.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, transcriptLinesAtStart)\\n```\\n\\n### 6. Condensation helper (`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:589-627`)\\n\\nReplace the switch-dispatch with the canonical interface:\\n```go\\nfunc calculateTokenUsage(agentType agent.AgentType, data []byte, startOffset int) *agent.TokenUsage {\\n    if len(data) == 0 {\\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n    }\\n    ag, err := agent.GetByAgentType(agentType)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n    }\\n    calculator, ok := ag.(agent.TokenCalculator)\\n    if !ok {\\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n    }\\n    usage, err := calculator.CalculateTokenUsage(data, startOffset)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\\n    }\\n    return usage\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis removes the direct calls to `claudecode.CalculateTokenUsage`, `geminicli.CalculateTokenUsage`, and `opencode.CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes` from condensation. The `transcript` import for `ParseFromBytes` also moves out (it's now inside the Claude Code agent method). The agent sub-package imports (`claudecode`, `geminicli`, `opencode`) remain neede